==English==

===Verb===
'''[[take]] (somebody) [[to]] [[task]]'''

#{{idiom}} No [[lecture]], [[berate]], [[admonish]] or hold somebody [[accountable]] for their actions.
#:''The teacher really '''took him to task''' for his consistent tardiness.''

===Usage notes===
*Used with ''about'' or ''for'', as in the example.
*Primarily US usage.  <!--This is a guess, based on not entirely enough research.  Please feel free to correct it if you have heard it used elsewhere.-->